Consider now that we perturb our system with an externally applied time-dependen
t force 
\begin_inset Formula $F(t)$
\end_inset

, such that system is instead described by the Hamiltonian
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
H(t)=H_{\text{eq}}+H_{\text{per}}(t)=\sum_{\alpha\beta}\left(h_{\alpha\beta}+B_{\alpha\beta}F(t)\right)c_{\alpha}^{\dagger}c_{\beta}+\frac{1}{2}\sum_{\alpha\beta\gamma\delta}V_{\gamma\delta}^{\alpha\beta}c_{\alpha}^{\dagger}c_{\beta}^{\dagger}c_{\gamma}c_{\delta}.
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $B_{\alpha\beta}$
\end_inset

