\begin_inset Formula $\text{\ref{eq:H_syst}}$
\end_inset

) and make a doubling of the degrees of freedom.
 We re-write it as
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
H(t) & =\frac{1}{2}\sum_{\alpha\beta}\bar{h}_{\alpha\beta}\left(c_{\alpha}^{\dagger}c_{\beta}-c_{\beta}c_{\alpha}^{\dagger}\right)+\frac{1}{4}\sum_{\alpha\beta\gamma\delta}V_{\gamma\delta}^{\alpha\beta}\left(c_{\alpha}^{\dagger}c_{\beta}^{\dagger}c_{\gamma}c_{\delta}+c_{\delta}c_{\gamma}c_{\beta}^{\dagger}c_{\alpha}^{\dagger}\right)+\frac{1}{2}\sum_{\alpha}\tilde{h}_{\alpha\alpha}
\end{align}

\end_inset

where we defined the quantity 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{h}_{\alpha\beta}(t)\equiv\tilde{h}_{\alpha\beta}(t)+\mu_{\alpha\beta}$
